From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: win32u/opengl: Android GLES desktop-GL bring-up + framebuffer fixes

Brings wine's win32u OpenGL path up on Android's system EGL (GLES-only, no
desktop EGL_OPENGL_API / no EGL_PLATFORM_SURFACELESS_MESA): fall back to
eglGetDisplay(EGL_DEFAULT_DISPLAY), accept GLES2/3 configs, bind
EGL_OPENGL_ES_API + force a modern (>=3.0) GLES context version, drop the
WGL flag/profile-mask attribs that make eglCreateContext fail on GLES, and
relax the mandatory-extension checks Android doesn't advertise. Plus the
double-buffer FBO present read-attachment fix and NULL-hardening in
opengl_drawable_set_context. Consolidated 2026-06-13 into a single diff
against the pinned base (was two concatenated diffs with shifted offsets
that no longer applied cleanly). Retains the gated vstpoc-gl ERR diagnostics
present in the shipped build. See project_zink_layer3_state /
feedback_xserver_gpu_glx_egl.

